WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.320
Chapter 1. Going nowhere.

00:06.160 --> 00:10.560
Huminda looked at her watch, and then at the traffic outside.

00:10.560 --> 00:16.080
The airport was 10km away, and it was already 5.15pm.

00:17.520 --> 00:20.960
Isn't there a quicker way to get to the airport?

00:20.960 --> 00:24.480
My plane leaves in less than two hours.

00:24.480 --> 00:26.680
She asked the taxi driver.

00:27.640 --> 00:29.880
Are you going home for Christmas?

00:29.880 --> 00:33.800
He smiled. The taxi was full of decorations.

00:34.600 --> 00:39.800
There was green tinsel on the steering wheel, and mistletoe under the mirror.

00:40.920 --> 00:46.520
Yes, said Huminda. But there was no Christmas spirit in her voice.

00:47.640 --> 00:51.560
Huminda looked out of the window, trying not to cry.

00:52.520 --> 00:56.360
She remembered the phone call from her mum earlier that day.

00:57.480 --> 00:59.560
She missed her parents so much.

01:00.440 --> 01:04.440
Their argument four years ago seemed stupid now.

01:05.800 --> 01:09.160
Thirty minutes later, they arrived at Galway Airport.

01:10.280 --> 01:12.440
How much is it? She asked.

01:13.480 --> 01:16.440
15 euros for you, sweetheart.

01:16.440 --> 01:18.760
Said the taxi driver with a smile.

01:19.640 --> 01:24.760
Huminda gave him a 20 euro note, and got quickly out of the taxi.

01:25.640 --> 01:27.560
Don't forget your change.

01:27.560 --> 01:31.800
shouted the taxi driver, with a 5 euro note in his hand.

01:32.520 --> 01:36.360
But Huminda was already inside the airport terminal.

01:37.640 --> 01:44.680
There were a lot of people, and Huminda pushed through the crowd to look at the screens for her flight.

01:44.680 --> 01:46.680
Cancelled.

01:48.040 --> 01:51.320
Stay calm and read it again. Slowly.

01:52.280 --> 01:54.360
You've read it wrong. That's all.

01:54.360 --> 01:54.920
She thought.

01:56.280 --> 02:00.040
Flight. Z-X-Y-247.

02:00.760 --> 02:05.240
Destination. London stansted. Cancelled.

02:06.440 --> 02:10.920
All flights from Galway were cancelled, because of bad weather.

02:11.800 --> 02:16.760
I'm sorry, but tomorrow's flight to London is fully booked.

02:17.560 --> 02:19.960
Christmas is a busy time of year.

02:21.080 --> 02:26.200
Said the man at the ticket office, when Huminda tried to find another flight.

02:27.560 --> 02:31.160
What about another airport? Dublin perhaps.

02:31.720 --> 02:32.120
Sorry.

02:32.680 --> 02:34.440
You don't understand.

02:35.000 --> 02:35.880
Said Huminda.

02:36.680 --> 02:39.800
I have to get to London as soon as possible.

02:40.600 --> 02:41.720
My dad's ill.

02:42.600 --> 02:47.720
I really am very sorry, the man said sympathetically.

02:48.680 --> 02:50.040
You could hire a car.

02:50.840 --> 02:55.400
It's a long journey, but if you need to get there quickly,

02:56.760 --> 03:03.800
as Huminda ran towards car hire, she saw that there were only two women waiting,

03:03.800 --> 03:05.880
and she started to feel hopeful.

03:06.840 --> 03:09.240
I'm sorry, but this is the last car.

03:09.800 --> 03:11.880
She heard the assistant say.

03:11.880 --> 03:14.200
But I was here first.

03:14.200 --> 03:17.000
Shouted a tall blonde woman.

03:17.000 --> 03:18.840
Only because you pushed in front of me.

03:19.480 --> 03:22.840
I'm getting married in three days. I have to get to London.

03:23.480 --> 03:26.520
Shouted an Irish girl in her late 20s.

03:27.240 --> 03:30.760
And I've got a very important audition.

03:30.760 --> 03:31.880
Said the blonde woman.

03:32.840 --> 03:34.200
Excuse me.

03:34.200 --> 03:35.400
Interrupted, Huminda.

03:36.200 --> 03:38.520
Did you say that there's only one car?

03:39.000 --> 03:41.080
Yes, and it's mine.

03:41.080 --> 03:43.080
Said the blonde, arrogantly.

03:43.080 --> 03:44.040
No, it's not.

03:44.920 --> 03:46.600
The argument continued.

03:47.160 --> 03:51.880
Huminda wanted to cry, but then she had an idea.

03:53.320 --> 03:57.160
If you two are going to London, we can share the car.

03:57.960 --> 03:58.680
What do you think?

03:59.640 --> 04:01.960
We can share the driving and the cost.

04:03.080 --> 04:05.960
The two women looked at her in silence.

04:06.760 --> 04:09.000
They probably think I'm mad.

04:09.000 --> 04:10.440
Thought Huminda.

04:11.080 --> 04:12.760
But that didn't worry her.

04:13.400 --> 04:18.120
The only thing that worried her was getting to London to see her family.

04:19.480 --> 04:22.840
Well, if you want to get to your audition.

04:23.400 --> 04:25.240
Huminda said to the blonde.

04:26.040 --> 04:28.440
And if you want to get married.

04:29.080 --> 04:30.760
She said to the other woman.

04:31.640 --> 04:33.880
Well, you've got no choice.

04:34.840 --> 04:37.640
Huminda was speaking angrily.

04:37.640 --> 04:41.400
And after a moment, the two women reluctantly agreed.

04:42.200 --> 04:44.600
Mr. O'Flaherty will be pleased.

04:44.600 --> 04:49.320
Thought Chrissie, the car hire assistant, as she showed the women their car.

04:51.080 --> 04:52.040
Chrissie!

04:52.040 --> 04:52.920
Chrissie!

04:52.920 --> 04:55.640
A man shouted, running towards them.

04:56.360 --> 04:59.720
It was very cold, but he was sweating.

04:59.720 --> 05:02.280
And his face was red and angry.

05:03.160 --> 05:04.680
Oh, that's my boss.

05:04.680 --> 05:05.960
Merry Christmas!

05:05.960 --> 05:08.200
She smiled and closed the door.

05:09.080 --> 05:10.280
Stop them, Chrissie!

05:11.240 --> 05:11.560
What?

05:12.280 --> 05:14.200
It's okay, Mr. O'Flaherty.

05:14.200 --> 05:15.240
They've paid?

05:15.240 --> 05:18.680
She smiled, waving at the car as it left.

05:19.640 --> 05:23.080
That car was reserved, you stupid girl.

05:23.080 --> 05:23.800
He shouted.

05:24.840 --> 05:26.600
Chrissie's face turned red.

05:27.240 --> 05:31.480
She didn't see the three businessmen as she ran into the airport,

05:31.480 --> 05:32.040
crying.

05:33.320 --> 05:35.640
Where is my car, Mr. O'Flaherty?

05:36.280 --> 05:36.920
Asked one.

05:37.800 --> 05:42.360
His voice was calm, but his gray eyes were dangerous.

05:43.640 --> 05:48.360
Colin O'Flaherty turned around nervously to talk to the three men.

05:49.240 --> 05:51.800
And he knew that he was in trouble.

05:53.080 --> 05:53.800
Big trouble.

05:53.960 --> 05:57.880
Chapter Two, Galway to Dublin.

06:04.360 --> 06:06.200
Don't worry, I'll be there.

06:07.000 --> 06:07.720
I love you too.

06:08.440 --> 06:12.360
Said Shauna, the Irish girl, she was on the phone.

06:13.800 --> 06:15.720
Was that your fiancé?

06:15.720 --> 06:18.600
Asked Haminde when Shauna finished speaking.

06:19.720 --> 06:20.520
Yes.

06:20.520 --> 06:22.200
She replied with a smile.

06:22.840 --> 06:25.960
And you're getting married on Christmas Eve.

06:26.680 --> 06:28.280
That's so romantic.

06:28.840 --> 06:29.320
I know.

06:30.040 --> 06:31.560
Graham is romantic.

06:31.560 --> 06:32.120
She said.

06:32.920 --> 06:36.680
She took a photo from her purse and gave it to Haminde.

06:37.400 --> 06:40.440
It was obvious that she loved him very much.

06:41.240 --> 06:43.480
He even proposed on Valentine's Day.

06:44.280 --> 06:45.640
Original.

06:45.640 --> 06:47.960
Said Vanessa, sarcastically.

06:47.960 --> 06:49.480
What is your problem?

06:49.560 --> 06:54.040
Replied Shauna, angry at the blonde woman's sarcastic reply.

06:55.160 --> 06:57.240
I'm not the one with the problem.

06:57.240 --> 06:59.240
I'm not the one getting married.

06:59.240 --> 06:59.880
Thank God.

07:00.600 --> 07:03.160
We left Galway two hours ago.

07:03.160 --> 07:08.280
And the only thing you've talked about is Gavin and how wonderful he is.

07:08.280 --> 07:09.480
His name's Graham.

07:10.120 --> 07:11.960
Graham, Gavin, whatever.

07:12.600 --> 07:13.720
So he's romantic.

07:14.360 --> 07:17.720
After six months of marriage, it won't be romantic.

07:17.720 --> 07:20.520
When you have to wash his dirty clothes every week.

07:21.400 --> 07:24.680
Vanessa, that's a horrible thing to say.

07:24.680 --> 07:25.560
Said Haminde.

07:26.280 --> 07:27.800
Have you never been in love?

07:29.000 --> 07:32.120
For a moment, Vanessa's eyes went dark.

07:33.160 --> 07:35.000
Love is for idiots.

07:35.000 --> 07:36.840
She said in a low voice.

07:38.280 --> 07:42.840
Shauna touched the small diamond engagement ring on her left hand

07:42.840 --> 07:46.200
and looked out of the window, trying not to cry.

07:47.160 --> 07:50.360
She loved Graham and he loved her.

07:50.920 --> 07:54.280
And on Christmas Eve, she was going to marry him.

07:55.560 --> 07:57.480
Don't listen to her, Shauna.

07:57.480 --> 07:58.520
Said Haminde.

07:59.560 --> 08:01.080
Shauna liked Haminde.

08:01.560 --> 08:05.480
She only looked about 22, but she seemed a lot older.

08:06.280 --> 08:10.920
At last thought Shauna when she saw a sign for Dublin Port.

08:11.560 --> 08:13.400
But Haminde didn't slow down.

08:14.040 --> 08:17.400
She was arguing with Vanessa and she didn't see it.

08:17.400 --> 08:18.920
Haminde, the port.

08:19.640 --> 08:21.240
You've just missed the exit.

08:21.240 --> 08:22.040
Said Shauna.

08:22.840 --> 08:24.520
What? Are you sure?

08:25.320 --> 08:28.280
Brilliant. This is all your fault.

08:28.280 --> 08:30.520
Shouted Vanessa at Shauna.

08:30.520 --> 08:31.240
My fault.

08:31.880 --> 08:33.160
Why is it my fault?

08:34.040 --> 08:36.120
Oh, don't start all that again.

08:37.000 --> 08:40.680
I'll turn off at the next exit and we'll come back.

08:40.680 --> 08:41.480
Said Haminde.

08:42.280 --> 08:46.120
But then the cars in front began to slow down and stop.

08:46.840 --> 08:48.600
That's all we need.

08:48.600 --> 08:50.040
A traffic jam.

08:50.040 --> 08:51.320
Said Vanessa.

08:51.320 --> 08:53.400
We'll never get there in time now.

08:54.520 --> 08:58.280
When they eventually arrived at the ferry terminal, it was late.

08:59.000 --> 09:01.880
There were no cars or passengers waiting.

09:01.880 --> 09:03.400
Only a security guard.

09:04.440 --> 09:07.000
Where do we go to get the ferry for Hollyhead?

09:07.000 --> 09:08.040
Shauna asked him.

09:08.680 --> 09:12.040
The security guard pointed behind him at the ferry,

09:12.040 --> 09:15.080
which was already sailing away from the port.

09:16.280 --> 09:16.680
No.

09:17.640 --> 09:19.080
They said at the same time.

09:20.440 --> 09:24.040
The next ferry is tomorrow morning, at 10 to 7.

09:24.040 --> 09:24.760
Said the guard.

09:25.640 --> 09:28.040
This is all your fault.

09:28.040 --> 09:29.080
Shouted Vanessa.

09:29.800 --> 09:31.080
Oh, shut up.

09:31.720 --> 09:33.880
Shauna and Haminde shouted back.

09:34.920 --> 09:37.240
Luckily, they found a small hotel.

09:38.120 --> 09:42.520
They started to relax as they began to take their bags out of the car

09:42.520 --> 09:43.800
in the hotel garage.

09:45.000 --> 09:46.840
Don't forget your briefcase.

09:46.840 --> 09:48.360
Haminde said to Vanessa.

09:49.160 --> 09:53.400
She was pointing at a dark brown expensive leather briefcase.

09:54.200 --> 09:55.480
It's not mine.

09:55.480 --> 09:56.760
Vanessa said.

09:56.760 --> 09:57.960
Pulling it from the car.

09:58.840 --> 10:00.040
It was quite heavy.

10:01.080 --> 10:03.240
Shauna, is it yours?

10:03.240 --> 10:03.560
No.

10:04.680 --> 10:06.600
And it's not mine.

10:06.600 --> 10:07.480
Said Haminde.

10:08.760 --> 10:12.280
So it was already in the car when we left the airport.

10:13.400 --> 10:15.560
Somebody has obviously forgotten it.

10:16.600 --> 10:18.840
What do you think is inside?

10:18.840 --> 10:19.640
Said Vanessa.

10:20.440 --> 10:23.880
And for the first time that day, she smiled.

10:28.440 --> 10:29.240
Chapter three.

10:30.280 --> 10:31.720
A sleepless night.

10:33.960 --> 10:35.720
I want to open it.

10:35.720 --> 10:36.520
Said Vanessa.

10:37.400 --> 10:39.240
But it's not ours.

10:39.240 --> 10:40.120
Said Haminde.

10:40.840 --> 10:45.480
It was one o'clock in the morning and she was in bed trying to sleep.

10:46.680 --> 10:51.320
We've got to be up in less than four hours if we want to get the first ferry.

10:52.040 --> 10:54.600
So please go to sleep.

10:55.560 --> 11:00.440
Vanessa turned away from the briefcase and pulled the blanket over her head.

11:01.480 --> 11:03.320
We couldn't open it anyway.

11:03.320 --> 11:04.280
It's locked.

11:04.360 --> 11:06.200
Said Shauna, getting into bed.

11:06.920 --> 11:09.640
But then she noticed Vanessa's smile.

11:09.640 --> 11:10.440
What?

11:10.440 --> 11:11.480
Why are you smiling?

11:12.360 --> 11:16.920
Vanessa took a clip from her hair and held it between her fingers.

11:17.640 --> 11:19.240
That'll never work.

11:19.240 --> 11:20.120
Laughed Shauna.

11:21.000 --> 11:23.160
It always works in films.

11:23.160 --> 11:24.280
Go on then.

11:24.280 --> 11:25.240
Said Shauna.

11:25.240 --> 11:25.640
Do it.

11:26.760 --> 11:29.560
Haminde pulled the blankets over her head.

11:30.360 --> 11:34.920
Vanessa worked on one of the locks using her clip as a key.

11:35.560 --> 11:36.600
I knew it.

11:36.600 --> 11:38.600
Said Shauna after a few minutes.

11:38.600 --> 11:40.760
I didn't think it was going to work.

11:40.760 --> 11:46.360
But before she could finish her sentence there was a click and the lock opened.

11:47.320 --> 11:49.000
Haminde sat up in bed.

11:49.960 --> 11:57.080
This didn't seem the right thing to do but now it was open she wanted to know what was inside.

11:57.880 --> 12:00.360
Vanessa soon opened the other lock.

12:01.240 --> 12:03.720
Slowly she opened the briefcase.

12:04.600 --> 12:09.880
Her eyes became big and round when she saw what was inside.

12:10.920 --> 12:13.560
Haminde watched their shocked faces.

12:15.000 --> 12:15.720
What's in it?

12:16.280 --> 12:16.760
Show me.

12:17.560 --> 12:19.800
Vanessa turned the case towards her.

12:20.440 --> 12:22.360
The briefcase was full of money.

12:23.320 --> 12:25.480
After a few moments Haminde said.

12:26.280 --> 12:29.480
There are hundreds of thousands of euros here.

12:30.040 --> 12:31.560
She laughed nervously.

12:32.600 --> 12:34.200
I've never seen so much money.

12:35.000 --> 12:37.000
There's only one thing we can do now.

12:37.880 --> 12:39.320
What are you doing?

12:39.320 --> 12:43.560
Vanessa said when she saw Haminde with her mobile phone in her hand.

12:44.520 --> 12:46.200
I'm going to phone the police.

12:47.080 --> 12:48.280
You can't do that.

12:48.920 --> 12:53.800
Do you realize what a difference this money could make to our lives?

12:54.600 --> 12:55.880
But it's not ours.

12:56.680 --> 12:58.120
We don't know who it is.

12:58.680 --> 13:00.360
There's no label, no name.

13:00.920 --> 13:01.960
Tell her Shauna.

13:03.080 --> 13:07.560
Shauna, you know we have to go to the police, don't you?

13:07.560 --> 13:08.440
Said Haminde.

13:09.240 --> 13:10.040
I don't know.

13:11.000 --> 13:13.400
My fiancé and I really want a honeymoon.

13:14.040 --> 13:16.520
We could go anywhere in the world with this money.

13:16.600 --> 13:21.400
The Maldives, the Caribbean, New York, San Francisco, anywhere.

13:22.360 --> 13:24.920
At the moment, we're going to stay in my parents' caravan.

13:25.880 --> 13:28.440
Shauna looked into Haminde's eyes.

13:29.880 --> 13:31.640
We've never had a holiday together.

13:32.680 --> 13:33.960
I'm sorry, Haminde.

13:34.840 --> 13:37.160
Vanessa held Haminde's hands.

13:37.800 --> 13:43.400
Her voice was soft and kind, and Haminde remembered that she was an actress.

13:44.200 --> 13:46.200
You said your dad's ill.

13:46.600 --> 13:47.720
Think about it.

13:48.200 --> 13:51.640
With this money, you could pay for the best doctors.

13:52.200 --> 13:54.280
Haminde's phone started to ring.

13:55.000 --> 13:58.280
Slowly, Haminde picked it up and answered.

13:59.400 --> 14:00.600
Hello.

14:01.000 --> 14:02.200
Oh, hello, Mum.

14:02.600 --> 14:03.800
How's Dad?

14:05.000 --> 14:11.000
When the phone call finished, ten minutes later, her cheeks were wet with tears.

14:11.800 --> 14:13.000
What is it, Haminde?

14:13.400 --> 14:14.200
Asked Shauna.

14:15.000 --> 14:17.000
My dad, he's got worse.

14:17.800 --> 14:19.800
They're not sure if he will survive.

14:21.000 --> 14:23.000
Vanessa closed the briefcase.

14:25.000 --> 14:27.000
Well, then, you need to get there quickly.

14:27.800 --> 14:31.800
If we go to the police now, they'll ask us questions for hours.

14:33.000 --> 14:33.800
Okay.

14:34.200 --> 14:35.800
Said Haminde quietly.

14:36.600 --> 14:38.600
Maybe not until tomorrow.

14:38.840 --> 14:40.360
Maybe not until tomorrow.

14:40.920 --> 14:41.960
Continued, Vanessa.

14:42.600 --> 14:43.800
I said, okay.

14:44.600 --> 14:50.600
We won't go to the police now, but when we get to London, after I've seen my dad, then we'll go.

14:51.560 --> 14:52.360
Do you all agree?

14:53.560 --> 14:57.480
Shauna nodded reluctantly, but Vanessa only said.

14:58.200 --> 15:00.200
Let's get a few hours' sleep now.

15:00.760 --> 15:02.600
We don't want to miss the next ferry.

15:03.800 --> 15:07.080
This time, they arrived early and waited in the car.

15:08.040 --> 15:12.920
It wasn't snowing, but it was cold, and everything looked very dark.

15:13.960 --> 15:19.960
When they started to drive onto the ferry, Haminde saw the face of the driver of the car behind her.

15:20.920 --> 15:23.080
That's strange, she thought.

15:23.960 --> 15:28.040
It's still dark outside, but he's wearing sunglasses.

15:29.160 --> 15:29.880
Are you okay?

15:30.440 --> 15:31.320
Asked Shauna.

15:31.960 --> 15:34.280
I'm cold, that's all.

15:34.840 --> 15:39.800
Haminde answered, but she didn't seem sure of what she was saying.

15:44.440 --> 15:47.480
Chapter four, on the ferry.

15:49.800 --> 15:56.440
It was dawn, and Shauna and Haminde looked at the red and orange sky over Dublin,

15:56.440 --> 15:58.840
as the ferry slowly left the port.

16:00.280 --> 16:02.840
When was the last time you saw your parents?

16:02.840 --> 16:04.280
Shauna asked Haminde.

16:05.400 --> 16:11.240
Four years ago, at my 18th birthday party, she answered sadly.

16:12.200 --> 16:14.280
Wow, that's a long time.

16:15.880 --> 16:20.360
They wanted me to marry someone else, somebody they chose.

16:21.080 --> 16:22.200
An arranged marriage?

16:22.920 --> 16:23.240
Yes.

16:23.800 --> 16:24.600
Said Haminde.

16:25.720 --> 16:27.720
They stood in silence for a while.

16:27.800 --> 16:34.360
In Indian tradition, a marriage is more than just a woman and a man being together.

16:35.480 --> 16:37.240
It's a marriage of two families.

16:38.840 --> 16:42.280
I've always known that it was very important to my family,

16:43.320 --> 16:44.760
but then I met Declan.

16:45.800 --> 16:51.240
I was only 17, that I knew that I wanted to spend the rest of my life with him,

16:52.360 --> 16:54.760
who we saw each other in secret for months.

16:55.560 --> 17:01.320
I was too frightened to tell my family about it, because they believe in arranged marriages.

17:02.840 --> 17:05.080
But then my parents told me the big news.

17:06.600 --> 17:13.000
At my 18th birthday party, they wanted to introduce me to my future husband, an Indian boy.

17:14.760 --> 17:16.760
I knew that I had to tell them the truth.

17:17.880 --> 17:19.000
I'm the only daughter.

17:19.960 --> 17:24.280
I've just got one brother, and my father was very angry.

17:25.640 --> 17:29.560
I had to choose, he told me, and I chose Declan.

17:30.360 --> 17:31.480
Are you still together?

17:32.200 --> 17:32.520
Yes.

17:33.240 --> 17:36.120
Said Haminde, and she touched her stomach.

17:37.800 --> 17:38.600
Are you pregnant?

17:39.240 --> 17:40.760
Shauna asked with a smile.

17:41.800 --> 17:42.120
Yes.

17:43.000 --> 17:45.160
I only got the news last week.

17:45.160 --> 17:45.800
She laughed.

17:46.920 --> 17:48.760
You're the only other person that knows.

17:49.480 --> 17:50.920
I haven't told Declan yet.

17:51.800 --> 17:54.760
I'm sure that when your dad knows, he'll be happy too.

17:56.120 --> 17:56.600
Maybe.

17:58.520 --> 18:01.080
Three hours later, they were in England.

18:01.880 --> 18:03.560
Haminde drove fast.

18:04.120 --> 18:07.880
They had to drive for another six hours before they arrived in London.

18:09.000 --> 18:13.800
After a few miles, Haminde noticed that Vanessa was looking over her shoulder.

18:14.760 --> 18:15.960
What's wrong, Vanessa?

18:16.920 --> 18:18.440
I... nothing.

18:18.440 --> 18:19.080
She said.

18:19.960 --> 18:21.320
Can't you drive faster?

18:22.040 --> 18:24.760
I'm already driving over the speed limit.

18:24.760 --> 18:25.080
Why?

18:26.280 --> 18:27.000
No reason.

18:27.480 --> 18:28.120
It's only...

18:28.920 --> 18:33.800
I don't want to frighten anyone, but I think somebody is following us.

18:34.520 --> 18:36.520
There's a dark blue car behind us.

18:37.080 --> 18:39.720
It's been there since we got on the ferry at Dublin.

18:40.680 --> 18:42.680
Haminde looked into the mirror.

18:43.320 --> 18:47.080
Her heart began to beat faster when she saw the sunglasses.

18:48.040 --> 18:49.880
Suddenly, they heard a horn.

18:50.760 --> 18:56.600
Haminde looked back at the road and saw that an enormous lorry was coming directly towards them.

18:57.480 --> 19:02.040
She turned the steering wheel to the right and pushed her foot down hard on the brake.

19:02.680 --> 19:04.280
But the lorry was getting nearer.

19:05.240 --> 19:07.000
The car seemed out of control.

19:07.720 --> 19:08.760
Someone screamed.

19:09.480 --> 19:11.560
But then the lorry passed by them.

19:12.520 --> 19:16.120
The car slowed down and Haminde's body relaxed.

19:17.240 --> 19:19.640
Suddenly, there was a loud noise.

19:20.680 --> 19:23.000
The three women all turned around.

19:23.720 --> 19:27.240
They saw the lorry crashing into the car that was following them.

19:31.800 --> 19:32.760
Chapter 5.

19:33.720 --> 19:35.160
The Road to London

19:37.320 --> 19:40.040
They drove the rest of the journey in silence.

19:41.000 --> 19:45.400
Three hours later, when they stopped to get petrol, they were still nervous.

19:46.360 --> 19:47.960
I need to get some air.

19:48.360 --> 19:50.600
Vanessa said, getting out of the car.

19:51.160 --> 19:52.520
Are you coming too, Shauna?

19:53.080 --> 19:54.600
Shauna shook her head.

19:55.400 --> 19:58.440
Vanessa didn't want to go anywhere by herself.

19:59.160 --> 20:00.440
She turned to Haminde.

20:01.160 --> 20:02.280
What about you?

20:02.280 --> 20:02.920
She asked.

20:04.120 --> 20:07.480
I want to leave as soon as I filled the car up with petrol.

20:07.480 --> 20:08.360
Said Haminde.

20:09.640 --> 20:14.520
Vanessa felt stupid for being so nervous, but she couldn't stop herself.

20:15.720 --> 20:19.480
In the toilets, she looked at herself in the mirror and laughed.

20:20.120 --> 20:21.640
She looked terrible.

20:22.440 --> 20:25.400
Without makeup, she looked older than 35.

20:26.360 --> 20:27.640
But she was alive.

20:28.760 --> 20:35.080
When Ben left her for her best friend, she was only 25 with the lead role in a musical

20:35.080 --> 20:37.560
that was going to take her all over the world.

20:38.360 --> 20:44.040
But she gave it all up because she loved him and she didn't want to be away from him.

20:45.400 --> 20:47.400
In the end, he left her anyway.

20:48.600 --> 20:52.280
There were other boyfriends, but for the last 10 years,

20:52.280 --> 20:56.920
she never really loved anyone else because she never wanted to be hurt again.

20:58.120 --> 21:04.280
She was never afraid of anything because there was nothing left to lose until today.

21:05.480 --> 21:09.000
Now, after the crash, things were different.

21:09.880 --> 21:11.720
Vanessa wanted to live.

21:12.520 --> 21:13.960
She wanted to change.

21:15.400 --> 21:17.240
Why didn't she listen to Haminde?

21:18.360 --> 21:20.360
Why didn't they go to the police before?

21:21.560 --> 21:23.240
Now it was too late.

21:24.600 --> 21:26.280
Why did she never listen?

21:28.120 --> 21:30.840
She went inside and ordered a cup of coffee.

21:31.640 --> 21:34.520
The person behind the bar was reading a newspaper.

21:35.320 --> 21:39.160
Vanessa saw the date, the 22nd of December.

21:40.280 --> 21:42.200
They only left Galway yesterday.

21:43.000 --> 21:44.440
It seemed a lot longer.

21:45.800 --> 21:48.760
There was a small television on the wall over the bar.

21:49.720 --> 21:50.600
The news was on.

21:52.520 --> 21:56.280
A body was found in the car park of Galway Airport, Ireland,

21:56.280 --> 21:58.520
in the early hours of this morning.

21:58.520 --> 22:00.920
A 33-year-old Colin O'Flahity,

22:00.920 --> 22:05.320
manager of a car hire at Galway Airport, was shot in the chest.

22:05.320 --> 22:08.280
The police believed the killing was related to drug trafficking.

22:09.640 --> 22:11.400
It's terrible, isn't it?

22:11.400 --> 22:14.520
Said the barman, passing Vanessa her glass of water.

22:15.560 --> 22:18.520
Vanessa realized that she was staring at the television.

22:19.160 --> 22:22.520
Her face was white, her mouth opened.

22:23.400 --> 22:24.760
It's in the newspapers.

22:25.560 --> 22:25.800
Look.

22:26.840 --> 22:28.360
He passed her the newspaper.

22:29.400 --> 22:33.000
Family man killed in drug shooting, said the headline.

22:33.880 --> 22:37.640
In the center of the page, there was a photo of Colin O'Flahity

22:37.640 --> 22:39.640
on holiday with his three-year-old son.

22:40.760 --> 22:42.680
They were obviously on a boat,

22:42.760 --> 22:45.240
and Colin was holding a very big fish.

22:46.360 --> 22:47.800
They looked so happy.

22:49.240 --> 22:51.000
Vanessa felt sick.

22:52.040 --> 22:53.640
She looked back at the television.

22:54.280 --> 22:55.800
A young woman was crying.

22:56.760 --> 22:59.320
At the bottom of the screen, Vanessa read,

23:00.280 --> 23:05.080
Mrs. Moira O'Flahity, Mr. O'Flahity's wife.

23:06.360 --> 23:09.160
If anyone knows anything, anything at all,

23:09.160 --> 23:12.680
please, for my little boy, please contact the police.

23:13.720 --> 23:16.440
Her voice sounded more and more desperate.

23:17.320 --> 23:20.840
Vanessa felt like the woman was talking directly to her.

23:21.800 --> 23:24.120
Anything at all, please.

23:24.680 --> 23:26.520
Vanessa couldn't hear any more.

23:27.160 --> 23:31.160
She ran from the bar, still holding the newspaper in her left hand.

23:32.120 --> 23:35.880
Chapter 6, Act the Hospital.

23:38.040 --> 23:38.600
Go on.

23:39.480 --> 23:41.640
We'll wait here for you, said Shauna.

23:42.440 --> 23:44.040
But what if they come back?

23:45.000 --> 23:46.520
You saw that accident.

23:46.520 --> 23:48.680
We'll be all right for a couple of hours.

23:48.680 --> 23:50.520
Insisted, Vanessa.

23:51.240 --> 23:53.640
Huminda looked nervously at the hospital.

23:54.200 --> 23:57.080
She took a deep breath and got out of the car.

23:57.320 --> 24:00.040
She took a deep breath and got out of the car.

24:01.320 --> 24:05.720
I'll be as quick as I can, but this is my mobile number if you need me.

24:06.600 --> 24:09.480
She quickly wrote it down and gave it to Shauna.

24:10.440 --> 24:14.120
Inside the hospital, Huminda took the lift to the ninth floor.

24:14.840 --> 24:18.280
When the doors opened, her little brother was waiting for her.

24:19.080 --> 24:21.000
But he wasn't so little anymore.

24:21.880 --> 24:26.120
The last time she saw him, he was nine years old, a child.

24:27.000 --> 24:31.240
Now, he was thirteen, and he was a lot taller than Huminda.

24:32.280 --> 24:34.840
There were so many things she wanted to ask him.

24:35.560 --> 24:37.560
But she could only say his name.

24:38.680 --> 24:39.240
Perindra.

24:40.280 --> 24:41.480
What is she doing here?

24:42.120 --> 24:44.120
Her father's voice interrupted them.

24:45.160 --> 24:48.920
He was seriously ill, but his voice was still strong.

24:49.640 --> 24:52.360
Meena, did you ask her to come here?

24:53.320 --> 24:58.120
Meena, Huminda's mother, looked elegant in a red silk sari.

24:59.000 --> 25:03.080
When she saw her daughter, there were tears of happiness in her eyes.

25:04.360 --> 25:08.120
Dad, oh Dad, I've missed you so much.

25:09.000 --> 25:10.680
Huminda ran towards him.

25:11.400 --> 25:15.560
His face was gray, his hair was thinner than she remembered,

25:16.120 --> 25:17.880
and he looked old and weak.

25:18.760 --> 25:22.840
But his eyes were angry, just like they were four years ago.

25:23.640 --> 25:24.920
I don't want you here.

25:25.640 --> 25:26.840
You made your decision.

25:28.040 --> 25:28.680
Please leave.

25:29.560 --> 25:35.560
Huminda touched his hand, but he closed his eyes and turned away from her.

25:37.160 --> 25:38.520
But I've come from Ireland.

25:39.320 --> 25:41.240
Dad, please listen to me.

25:41.720 --> 25:42.600
Dad!

25:42.600 --> 25:46.360
She shouted as they took him into the operating room on a trolley.

25:46.920 --> 25:48.920
Meena and Perindra next to him.

25:50.200 --> 25:51.560
I love you, Dad.

25:51.560 --> 25:53.800
She said, but he was gone.

25:55.080 --> 25:58.040
She was alone in the long white corridor.

25:59.080 --> 26:03.320
She sat down, put her head in her hands, and cried.

26:04.360 --> 26:07.720
All her hopes of a happy reunion were gone.

26:08.760 --> 26:11.400
It was not going to be easy for him to meet her again.

26:12.040 --> 26:16.520
Huminda knew that, but she didn't think it was going to be this difficult.

26:17.800 --> 26:21.240
Why didn't he understand that she never wanted to choose?

26:22.440 --> 26:27.160
Why couldn't he see that she was still his daughter, still his little girl?

26:28.520 --> 26:34.440
Why couldn't he see that she still needed her dad, even if she loved Declan?

26:35.240 --> 26:42.760
When she couldn't cry anymore, she stood up and decided to go with Shauna and Vanessa to the police station.

26:44.360 --> 26:51.880
Later on, I'll come back, and I won't leave until he understands, she thought, as she went outside.

26:52.840 --> 26:58.360
When she got to the car park, the car was there, but there was no Shauna and Vanessa.

26:59.480 --> 27:02.040
And there was no briefcase, full of money.

27:05.080 --> 27:09.560
Chapter 7, Danger Money

27:12.120 --> 27:16.920
Shauna and Vanessa were in the back of the car. Their hands were tied.

27:17.560 --> 27:22.520
They were very frightened as they tried to listen to the conversation of the two men in front of them.

27:24.520 --> 27:27.480
What are you going to do with your 10% of the money, Steve?

27:28.280 --> 27:33.160
I'd like to go on an ice holiday. Somewhere out. What about you?

27:34.600 --> 27:40.200
Vanessa looked at the two men. She had to concentrate. She had to think of a plan,

27:40.760 --> 27:45.160
and she needed to think quickly. But she could only think of one thing.

27:45.960 --> 27:48.360
Colleen O'Flahat is three-year-old son.

27:49.720 --> 27:54.760
While they were waiting for Huminda outside the hospital, these two men came up to them.

27:55.240 --> 27:59.960
They were smiling and seemed nice when they asked for directions to King's cross station.

28:00.600 --> 28:06.040
But when Shauna was pointing the best way to them, the two men pushed them both into their car.

28:06.840 --> 28:08.280
They wanted the briefcase.

28:10.600 --> 28:14.520
Did you see that crash between the lorry and the car with the plank-lose police?

28:15.640 --> 28:21.720
Laugh, Steve. He saw the way Vanessa and Shauna looked at each other, suddenly realising the truth.

28:22.760 --> 28:29.000
Did you think that was us? Laugh the driver. They thought that was us in that accident.

28:30.760 --> 28:33.080
And they laughed even louder.

28:33.720 --> 28:37.720
Just then, their telephone rang. The driver answered the call.

28:38.920 --> 28:43.720
Yes, boss. Okay. The old building in East London.

28:44.600 --> 28:50.200
Of course we've got the money. We're not stupid. And the two ladies.

28:51.560 --> 28:58.600
No. There were only two. What do you mean there's another one? You'll have to go and get her.

28:59.960 --> 29:07.320
Vanessa knew then what she had to do. Carefully, she pulled her mobile phone from her coat pocket

29:07.320 --> 29:18.280
and started to write a text message. You are in danger. Men taking us to building in East London.

29:18.280 --> 29:28.440
Be careful. Man coming for you. Go to police. S and V.

29:30.280 --> 29:33.240
It seemed to take forever to write the short message.

29:34.120 --> 29:38.120
She took out the piece of paper with Haminda's number on it and typed

29:38.200 --> 29:42.040
three five four seven eight one two double three oh.

29:43.320 --> 29:47.960
Now she only needed to press send and then Haminda could get help.

29:49.080 --> 29:55.640
Aye. What are you doing? Give me that. Steve turned around and tried to grab the phone.

29:56.200 --> 30:00.920
Vanessa tried to press send but he was pulling the phone out of her hand.

30:01.800 --> 30:07.480
Leave her alone. Shouted Shauna pulling on his arm trying to free Vanessa.

30:08.280 --> 30:14.200
The driver was looking at them and couldn't control the car anymore. Steve got out his gun

30:14.200 --> 30:21.080
but Shauna pushed him and he dropped it. Yes. Stupid woman. He shouted as he looked

30:21.080 --> 30:26.360
desperately around his feet for it. Just then a police siren sounded in the distance.

30:27.080 --> 30:31.000
Steve looked up and saw that the police car was blocking the road in front of them.

30:31.640 --> 30:37.640
Its blue light was bright in the dark evening. The driver pushed his foot down hard on the break.

30:38.440 --> 30:43.880
Shauna realized with horror that they were going straight for it too fast.

30:44.760 --> 30:50.840
The car began to move from side to side dangerously out of control. Vanessa screamed.

30:51.480 --> 30:58.600
Shauna held her breath ready for the crash. She closed her eyes waiting. Her body went

30:58.600 --> 31:05.400
quickly forwards and then back but there was no crash. When she was sure that the car wasn't

31:05.480 --> 31:11.880
moving anymore she slowly opened her eyes. The car was just a few centimeters from a police car.

31:13.000 --> 31:18.680
Suddenly a lot of policemen were all around the car and Shauna could finally breathe.

31:19.720 --> 31:21.640
Their nightmare was over.

31:26.600 --> 31:30.280
Chapter 8. Haminda Alone

31:31.240 --> 31:36.600
I'm sure they think I'm really stupid. Thought Haminda.

31:37.640 --> 31:40.200
And I am because I believed them.

31:42.120 --> 31:45.480
Spend time with your dad before his operation, they said.

31:46.840 --> 31:53.000
They weren't worried about me spending time with dad. The only thing they wanted was enough

31:53.000 --> 31:57.880
time to escape with the money. Vanessa didn't want to go to the police.

31:58.600 --> 32:05.720
She said that very clearly but Shauna. Shauna was different. At least Haminda

32:05.720 --> 32:11.800
thought Shauna was different. She thought that after all this was over they could be friends.

32:12.760 --> 32:15.720
But now she didn't know what to think anymore.

32:17.560 --> 32:20.760
Maybe they've gone to get a drink or something to eat.

32:20.840 --> 32:23.800
Thought Haminda. But she knew the truth.

32:24.920 --> 32:30.760
Without Haminda there to stop her Vanessa probably talked to Shauna about all the places

32:30.760 --> 32:37.320
Shauna could go on her honeymoon. They could share the money. Half each. 50-50.

32:38.120 --> 32:41.080
That was enough to go on honeymoon for over three months.

32:42.200 --> 32:49.560
Haminda could hear Vanessa. It was so easy to believe her. She was the perfect actress.

32:51.000 --> 32:58.200
Excuse me. Said a gentle voice making Haminda jump. Sorry I didn't want to frighten you.

32:59.320 --> 33:06.520
Haminda turned around and saw a young man. He was smiling kindly and when Haminda saw that his

33:06.520 --> 33:13.640
arm was in a plaster she started to relax. No I'm sorry. How can I help?

33:14.680 --> 33:19.560
Can you tell me the way to Kings Cross station? I came here in an ambulance

33:19.640 --> 33:24.040
but I don't know this part of London and I'm not sure how to get back home from here.

33:25.320 --> 33:29.960
I don't know but I've got a map in the car. Said Haminda.

33:31.000 --> 33:37.320
She was about to put the key in the door when her mobile phone beeped. She had a new message.

33:38.200 --> 33:45.400
She took the phone out of her pocket and began to read. You are in danger.

33:46.200 --> 33:53.880
No. This can't be happening. These things happen in films. Not to people like me.

33:53.880 --> 34:00.680
She thought reading the message a second time. She looked up slowly at the reflection of the

34:00.680 --> 34:08.120
man in the car window. For a moment she couldn't believe what she saw. She was too frightened to

34:08.200 --> 34:15.560
breathe. He was taking off the plaster. It was fake. He didn't have a broken arm.

34:16.600 --> 34:25.160
He was taking something out of his jacket. Then Haminda realized what it was. He was pulling out a gun.

34:25.160 --> 34:33.080
Chapter 9. Back Together.

34:35.800 --> 34:40.280
Just a minute. Said Haminda. She looked around,

34:40.280 --> 34:46.920
careful not to alarm the gunman. But the car park was dark and empty. There was nobody to ask

34:46.920 --> 34:53.560
for help. In the glass of the car window she saw him raise the gun. Without thinking,

34:53.560 --> 34:58.840
she turned around and surprised him with a powerful kick. The man fell back.

34:58.840 --> 35:05.240
The gun dropped to the floor and went under the car. His head hit the side of the car and he fell

35:05.240 --> 35:11.080
to the ground. Haminda didn't wait for him to wake up. She quickly darred the number of the

35:11.080 --> 35:18.520
emergency services. 9. 9. 9. Every second seemed like a year as she listened to the ringing.

35:18.600 --> 35:25.800
Then a woman's voice answered. Emergency services. Which service do you require? Police, ambulance or

35:25.800 --> 35:36.120
fire? And Haminda started to cry. Police, please. Hello. Police. There's a man with a gun. He wants

35:36.120 --> 35:42.440
to shoot me. I'm outside the Queen Elizabeth Hospital in London. But before she could finish

35:42.440 --> 35:50.200
telling the operator everything, there was a loud bang, pain and then for Haminda everything

35:50.200 --> 36:01.160
went black. Haminda could see lights, bright white lights and her first thought was that she was dead.

36:02.760 --> 36:08.760
But then she felt someone touch her hand and her mother's sweet voice said her name.

36:09.480 --> 36:16.600
Slowly, Haminda opened her eyes and her mother's face slowly became clear.

36:18.760 --> 36:30.120
Mum, it's all right my darling. What happened? Where am I? You were shot but you're going to be fine.

36:30.760 --> 36:38.280
You're in hospital. What about my baby? Haminda started to feel frightened.

36:39.160 --> 36:47.320
Your baby's fine. Haminda saw that there were tears in her mother's eyes but they were tears of

36:47.320 --> 36:54.600
happiness. I'm going to be a grandmother. Haminda looked around the room.

36:55.560 --> 37:03.960
Perindra was there. Even Shauna and Vanessa were there. Everyone except her dad and Declan.

37:05.400 --> 37:06.200
Where were they?

37:07.880 --> 37:14.360
What day is it? Asked Haminda. It's Christmas Eve. You're getting married.

37:15.480 --> 37:22.120
And what about your audition, Vanessa? I got the part of course. It's a thriller about some

37:22.200 --> 37:26.360
dangerous criminals. We're starting filming next week in France.

37:27.160 --> 37:31.880
And I'm getting married in? Shauna looked excitedly at the clock.

37:31.880 --> 37:37.880
About three hours from now. I really must go now. My mum is waiting for me with my dress.

37:38.600 --> 37:43.560
But I just wanted to see you before. We wanted to know that you were okay.

37:43.560 --> 37:50.600
Smiled Vanessa. There was only one more thing Haminda wanted to know but she was also afraid

37:50.600 --> 37:51.800
of hearing the answer.

37:53.320 --> 37:56.440
Mum, how did dad's operation go?

37:57.000 --> 38:03.080
Haminda asked. But before Mina could answer, the door to Haminda's room opened.

38:03.960 --> 38:08.120
I hope this young man drives his car better than he does a wheelchair.

38:08.120 --> 38:13.960
Said Haminda's father. Declan pushed him into the room and next to Haminda's bed.

38:14.920 --> 38:24.520
I love you. Declan whispered and kissed her gently on the lips. Then Haminda's father took her hand.

38:25.720 --> 38:33.960
Haminda, when I heard you were shocked and in danger of dying, I thought about all those years.

38:35.240 --> 38:40.520
I realized that what is important is that you're happy. And if it is Declan?

38:41.400 --> 38:46.920
He reached up for Declan's hand. That makes you happy. Then I am happy.

38:48.200 --> 38:53.640
Seeing her tears, he looked suddenly worried. You are happy, aren't you?

38:55.080 --> 39:06.360
Yes, she said quietly. I am now. Now that my family is back together.

